{"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Describe your app’s structure declaratively, much like you declare a view’s","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"appearance. Create a type that conforms to the App protocol and use it to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"enumerate the Scenes that represent aspects of your app’s user interface.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OpenSwiftUI enables you to write code that works across all of Apple’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"platforms, Linux and Windows. However, it also enables you to tailor your app to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the specific capabilities of each platform. For example, if you need to respond"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to the callbacks that the system traditionally makes on a UIKit, AppKit, or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"WatchKit app’s delegate, define a delegate object and instantiate it in your app"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"structure using an appropriate delegate adaptor property wrapper, like"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"UIApplicationDelegateAdaptor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For platform-specific design guidance, see "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/design\/human-interface-guidelines\/platforms"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in the Human Interface Guidelines for Apple Platform and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/learn.microsoft.com\/windows\/apps\/design"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for Windows."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"topicSections":[{"identi